The paper deals with object detection and classification using deep learning-based approaches for autonomous driving, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel method for identifying mistakes made by object detectors, which involves using a binary classifier and features extracted from temporal and stereo inconsistencies, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the safety-critical nature of autonomous driving and the need to detect errors, which falls under the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
